       Ominous and Akron begin thier exit of the conference room. Ominous 
hopes Zardus will think about the offer. "Yes Zardus, we will be using 
regular communication frequences. Call us at anytime you wish. Good luck 
eliminating the Maximals. Goodbye." And then began down the corridor for his 
vessle.
       "Sir, why didnt you tell him about the Distillment Chamber?" Akron 
asked. Ominous realized she was such a nieve, yet deadly, bot. And didnt know 
when to keep her mouth shut.
       "He dosent need to know of it yet, it would just confuse him anyhow. 
And we would have to make it bigger to fit all of his forces inside, so lets 
just see if he sides with us or not before we go and rip it apart." And then 
put a finger over his lips, silently telling her to shut her mouth.

       Hell Beast shivered. He didnt know what was wrong with him, but 
whatever it was, it was nasty. Vomiting and dysentary set in earlier. Now 
with the shakes he couldnt stop coughing.
       "As soon as we hear from Darkmouse, we'll get you that Liquid Energon. 
So, until then, sleep." Aquarious instructed.

       Black Aracnia waited for Quasar. She didnt see her anywhere, but she 
mustve been on her way back from the battle. Aracnia knew that she hadnt 
payed much attention to her child, and with Quickstrike missing she would 
feel even more alone.
       "Hurry home Quasar." She mumbled to herself, as a cold wind swept over 
her frail body.

       Venus looked over the mapping grid. They were instructed to monitor 
the Artic, Ominous' old lair inparticular. A lone Predacon was heading towrds 
the Cave....Quasar.
       "Subcommander Putnam, should we take that bot?" Venus said, and turned 
to the blue eyed bot standing across the room.
       "Yes, get her and bring her back. It will send a message to the 
Predacons. And perhaps we can convert her." He finished, smiling.
       Venus nodded and went to prepare a shuttle to nab the little female 
Predacon. If she succedded, no doubt she would be rewarded.
